JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s trade balance swung to an unexpected surplus of R6.7 billion ($495 million) in September, from a revised R8.9 billion shortfall in August, data from the revenue agency showed on Monday.Exports rose 10.1% on a month-on-month basis, while imports were down 6.6%, the South African Revenue Service said.Analysts polled by Reuters had expected a trade deficit of R1.1 billion for September.($1 = R13.5220) 